==English==

===Etymology===
"not genuine," [[wikipedia:1900|1900]], phoney, perhaps an alteration of ''[[fawney]]'' "gilt brass ring used by swindlers" ([[wikipedia:1781|1781]]), from Ir. ''[[fáinne]]'' "ring."  The noun meaning "phony person or thing" is attested from [[wikipedia:1902|1902]].

===Alternative spellings===
* '''phony'''

===Adjective===
'''phoney'''
# Fraudulent; having a misleading appearance.

===Noun===
'''phoney'''
# A person who professes beliefs or opinions that he or she does not hold or assumes an identity other than their own.

===Synonyms===
* [[dissember]]
* [[phoney]]
